The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Indian shuttlers ooze confidence

 - Sudirman Cup 

Beijing: Notwithstanding the absence of Aparna Popat, Indian shuttlers are brimming with confidence ahead of their first encounter against Wales in the Sudirman Cup world mixed team badminton championship starting here Tuesday. 

?We are confident about Tuesdays tie against Wales though our opponents are ranked higher,? the teams Indonesian coach Hadi Sugiyanto said on the sidelines of a practice session on Monday. 

?All the players are fully fit and raring to go. We have a good chance of winning against Wales,? he said. 

He also expressed satisfaction over the group India is in, which also figures Wales, the US and Scotland. 

The nine-member Indian team consists of Anup Sridhar, Arvind Bhatt, Sanave Thomas, Rupesh Kumar, Jaseel Ismail, V Diju, Trupti Murgunde, Jwala Gutta and Shruti Kurien. 

Each tie in the meet comprises mens singles and doubles, womens singles and doubles, and mixed doubles matches. 

 (PTI) 




